# Calculatories.com — Project Context

Programmatic + editorial calculator site targeting US/UK/CA/AU traffic.
Monetized via Google AdSense (→ future SaaS pivot). Every public page must be
SEO-grade and ad-ready. Treat each page as a landing page that has to rank.

## Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript **strict**, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- Hosting: Vercel
- No `any`. Every component has an explicit props `interface`. ESLint + Prettier clean.
- Prefer Server Components; only mark `'use client'` where interactivity requires it.

## Canonical host (CRITICAL — do not mix)
- Single source of truth: `const SITE_URL = "https://calculatories.com"` (NO www).
- Use `SITE_URL` for `metadataBase`, every `canonical`, every `og:url`, and `sitemap.xml`.
- The Vercel redirect must send `www → non-www`. If you instead choose www as primary,
  flip ALL of the above to www — but never serve one host while canonicalizing the other.

## File structure per calculator
```
app/[category]/[slug]/
  page.tsx        # Server: metadata + JSON-LD + layout + ad slots
  calculator.tsx  # 'use client': inputs + instant calc logic
  content.tsx     # Server: What is / How to / formula / FAQ / related
```

## Categories
`finance`, `health`, `salary`, `tools`, `legal`, `productivity`

## Every page ships with
- Unique `<title>`, description, canonical, **per-page** OpenGraph AND Twitter meta
- JSON-LD: `WebApplication`/`SoftwareApplication` + `FAQPage` + `BreadcrumbList`
- Ad slots: `<HeaderAd/>`, `<InContentAd/>`, `<SidebarAd/>`
- ≥3 internal links, ≥800 words of body content, ≥1 formula or table
- Mobile-first; Core Web Vitals targets: LCP < 2.5s, CLS < 0.1

## Locale
US-first: USD default, imperial units with a metric toggle where relevant,
US spelling (`color`, not `colour`), current-year references kept up to date.
